ne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Edward Watkins VI was born in 1438, in Holwell, Dorset, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Edwards Watkins V, was 28 and his mother, Margaret Phillips, was 28. He married Margaret Aukhurst about 1472, in Holwell, Dorset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1498, in his hometown, at the age of 60, and was buried in Holwell, Dorset, England."},"et":{"1438–1498":"1438–1498","1434–1464":"1434–1464","1450–1487":"1450–1487","1473–1527":"1473–1527","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1410–1490":"1410–1490","1473":"1473","1450":"1450","1490":"1490","1478":"1478","1434":"1434","1455":"1455","1498":"1498","1410":"1410","1487":"1487","1464":"1464","about 1487":"umbes 1487","1527":"1527","1438":"1438","about 1472":"umbes 1472","Holwell, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Holwell, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holwell, Dorset, England":"Holwell, Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1438–1498":"1438–1498","1434–1464":"1434–1464","1450–1487":"1450–1487","1473–1527":"1473–1527","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1410–1490":"1410–1490","1473":"1473","1450":"1450","1490":"1490","1478":"1478","1434":"1434","1455":"1455","1498":"1498","1410":"1410","1487":"1487","1464":"1464","about 1487":"noin 1487","1527":"1527","1438":"1438","about 1472":"noin 1472","Holwell, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Holwell, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Holwell, Dorset, England":"Holwell, Dorset, England"},"fr":{"1438–1498":"1438–1498","1434–1464":"1434–1464","1450–1487":"1450–1487","1473–1527":"1473–1527","1410–1478":"1410–1478","1410–1490":"1410–1490","1473":"1473","1450":"1450","1490":"1490","1478